DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A derived program of the National Cancer Institute's Biorepositories and Biospecimen Research Branch (NCI BBRB) that carries out specialized biospecimen and data procurements to support biospecimen science activities. The caHUB network consists of Biospecimen Source Sites (BSSs), The Comprehensive Biospecimen Resource (CBR), The Comprehensive Data Resource (CDR), The Pathology Resource Center (PRC), and Molecular Analysis Facilities (MAFs)._Any specifically defined piece of work that is undertaken or attempted to meet a single requirement._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.
